That's a Maastrichtian-era fossil site. The Carchaodontosaurs didn't survive the Cenomanian-Turonian boundary event. Tyrannosaurs never made it to Africa or South America where the Carchs achieved their most massive sizes and they went extinct at roughly the same time the North American and Asian Carchs also went extinct during the Cenomanian-Turonian boundary event.
